{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, the Multilayer Perceptron (MLP) functions (Ruck et al. 1990) are used to combine the per-point features.",
    "RBF-VAE is the first module, and the segmentation (group convolution) is the second one, they are trained separately.",
    "As the loss function, they have used cross-entropy loss for segmentation (13):",
    "where L is the number of labels, p gt l is the probability of the ground truth label and p l is the probability of each label.",
    "While the work of Meng et al. (2019) presents a robust segmentation method, its performance is reduced in certain shapes, most probably due to the encoded 90 • symmetry."
  ]
}